      "side": 1,
      "message": "You don\u0027t actually need this check: https://stackoverflow.com/q/19034858\n\nI imagine you put this because you weren\u0027t sure, because memcmp docs aren\u0027t very clear on it (I had to hunt for this confirmation too!). If that\u0027s the case, consider `0 \u003d\u003d char_traits::compare(left.data(), right.data(), left.length())` instead? That does the same thing (in fact some specializations do just call `__builtin_memcmp`) but hopefully makes the intent clearer?",
      "range": {
